# Engagement-private operator-supplied source binaries (P9 cleanup of the SUEZ-WeBuy
# engagement; pattern generalised so future engagements can drop temporary
# operator-supplied audio / docx / xlsx into the workspace without polluting
# git). Redacted text extracts under docs/wip/intelligence/<engagement>/extracts/
# remain committed; the binaries themselves stay operator-private.
temp-delete-or-move/
temp-move-or-delete/
*.opus
*.m4a
*.mp3
*.wav
docs/wip/intelligence/**/*.docx
docs/wip/intelligence/**/*.pdf
docs/wip/intelligence/**/*.xlsx
docs/wip/intelligence/**/*.pptx

# I12/P12 follow-up — Think Big client-engagement folder shape (per WORKSPACE_BLUEPRINT_HOLISTIKA.md
# and BRAND_COBRANDING_PATTERN.md). Branded PDFs are tracked deliverables: this repo is shared
# with non-technical readers via git + Google Drive sync, and most stakeholders consume PDFs,
# not markdown. Track *.pdf + render-manifest.json (sha256 audit trail). Keep markdown sidecars
# ignored — they are render-time duplicates of the canonical sources in 01-operator-pack/ +
# 02-customer-pack/, and tracking them creates drift risk.
docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Think Big/Clients/*/_exports/*
!docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Think Big/Clients/*/_exports/.gitkeep
!docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Think Big/Clients/*/_exports/README.md
!docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Think Big/Clients/*/_exports/*.pdf
!docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Think Big/Clients/*/_exports/render-manifest.json

